										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Major Series E Funding Strengthens Flutterwave’s Market Position</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flutterwave raised $250 million in a Series E funding round that valued the company at $3.2 billion. To date they have received $123 million in the first part of this funding round and will subsequently receive further investment.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2016, Flutterwave has raised over $500 million so far and investors continue to remain bullish on them. Prior to this recent $250 million funding round Flutterwave received $170 million at a valuation of $1 billion, and later a further $250 million at a $3 billion valuation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Currently Flutterwave is operating what is the biggest payments network on the continent. Operating in thirty-five countries Flutterwave processes over $120 billion on a yearly basis. The company operates with a wide variety of partners merchants, banks, remittance companies and more.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flutterwave, founded by Olugbenga Agboola and Iyinoluwa Aboyeji developed a solution that helps to navigate the messy financial structures present throughout Africa enabling digital payments to be facilitated to businesses.</span></p>
<h2><b>Ripple Strategic Investment and Stablecoin Integration Strategy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ripple has joined the round as a strategic equity investor. While the size of its stake has not been disclosed, the partnership focuses on integrating Ripple’s RLUSD stablecoin into Flutterwave’s payment ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">RLUSD is a U.S. dollar-backed stablecoin designed to enable fast and efficient blockchain-based settlement. It reduces delays in cross-border transactions while minimizing friction from currency conversion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This is particularly relevant in African markets where multiple currencies and exchange volatility create operational challenges. The integration will connect Ripple Payments with Flutterwave’s infrastructure through </span><a href="https://www.ibm.com/think/topics/api" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">API</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">-based systems. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This enables settlement across banks, digital wallets, and card networks within a unified framework. The collaboration aims to expand stablecoin usage across high-volume African payment corridors and improve liquidity flows.</span></p>
<h2><b>Africa’s Cross-Border Payments Infrastructure Challenge<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202935" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202935" class="size-full wp-image-202935" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/a-futuristic-neon-lit-digital-poster-dep_bAw63PJhW7G7h1LM7M4X7g_T6Zynj9jTBCZrk1eLI6eIA.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing Africa’s fragmented payment systems alongside a blockchain-based stablecoin network enabling faster cross-border transactions." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202935" class="wp-caption-text">Africa’s complex payment landscape drives demand for stablecoin-powered solutions to enable faster, more predictable cross-border transactions. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The African continent is made up of 54 countries each with different monetary policies, currencies, and regulatory framework. Funds transfers often need to pass through many correspondent banks resulting in substantial cost increase and prolonged settlement period.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Currency conversions further add to complexity, hiding expenses and posing foreign exchange risk to transacting parties. All these inefficiencies negatively affect SMEs and large corporations equally, further amplifying the demand for faster, more predictable money movements.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In Nigeria, the local currency (the naira) and other regional currencies are currently under volatility. Consequently there has been growing interest in dollar-backed stable money transfer mechanisms. Stablecoins offer another form of predictable and faster settlement.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flutterwave connects banks, fintechs, and merchants through unified payment infrastructure across Africa.  Ripple views Africa as a key growth region for blockchain payments due to FX volatility and outdated payment systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ent-raises-100m-seed-workspace-security/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ent Raises $100M Seed Funding to Reinvent Cybersecurity for the AI Era</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Regulatory History and IPO Strategy Shift</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In 2022, Flutterwave found itself under regulatory investigation in Kenya after the government froze $51.9 million in company accounts. In March 2023, Kenyan courts threw out the case against the company.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Even so, regulatory approval in critical markets, such as Kenya and South Africa still lags behind. Increasingly, focus for Flutterwave is on ensuring it complies. This has influenced its long-term growth and licensing roadmap.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flutterwave has also adjusted its IPO strategy, shifting focus toward a potential listing in Lagos. This move reflects its operational base and evolving capital markets strategy. It also signals a preference for regional market alignment over immediate global listing ambitions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These efforts are underpinned by structural changes in the business. Headcount in certain geographies has been cut, aimed at streamlining operations and controlling costs and at bolstering the margins to enable sustainability in growth.</span></p>
