										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Ent Emerges From Stealth With $100M Funding Round</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ent has raised from stealth with $100 million in seed financing. The funding round was led by Decibel. Additional investors include Sequoia, Crosspoint Capital Partners, Craft Ventures, Shield Capital, Felicis, and In-Q-Tel.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is introducing an intent-aware workspace security platform designed for the AI era. Ent aims to help organisations prevent cyber incidents before they happen rather than responding after damage has already occurred.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded by Elias Manousos and Brandon Dixon, the team brings experience from RiskIQ, which was acquired by Microsoft, as well as Microsoft Security Copilot. The company believes artificial intelligence has fundamentally changed the cybersecurity landscape.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">According to Ent, AI-powered attacks have dramatically reduced the time between compromise and impact. Traditional security systems often identify threats only after harmful actions have already taken place. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ent’s approach focuses on detecting intent and stopping risky behaviour before incidents escalate. The new capital will support hiring, product development, AI governance capabilities, security integrations, and expansion of the company’s endpoint intelligence platform.</span></p>
<h2><b>Platform Monitors Human and AI Activity in Real Time</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ent’s platform operates directly within the customer’s cloud environment. This allows organisations to maintain full control and ownership of their data while benefiting from real-time security monitoring.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system uses a lightweight agent that observes behaviour across browsers, applications, workflows, local runtimes, and data movement. It analyses both human actions and AI agent activity to determine intent at the moment decisions are made.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Customer-defined security policies are then applied immediately. When risky behaviour is detected, the platform can trigger interventions before data loss, policy violations, or security breaches occur.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlike traditional endpoint security tools, Ent focuses on understanding why an action is happening rather than simply recording what happened afterwards. The company argues that intent awareness creates a new layer of security that existing products cannot provide.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growing Enterprise Demand Supports Early Adoption<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202931" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202931" class="size-full wp-image-202931" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/a-futuristic-neon-lit-cybersecurity-post_M46HQ5wHUim24CaHcNdiKA_ApO3NiqwQIurRWGygXFImA_cover.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing an AI cybersecurity system monitoring behaviour and preventing threats in real time." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202931" class="wp-caption-text">Ent secures $100M to advance intent-aware cybersecurity and prevent threats before they happen. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Despite operating in stealth mode until now, Ent has already secured Global 2000 customers across several industries. These include organisations in hospitality, financial services, and defence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Customers use the platform to address insider threats, AI risks, incidents. The system provides behavioural context helping security teams understand action reasoning and determine appropriate responses effectively.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As AI becomes more deeply integrated into business operations, organisations face new governance challenges. Employees and AI agents increasingly interact with sensitive information across multiple applications and workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ent believes existing security products were designed for a different era. Most rely on signals generated after user actions occur. The company instead evaluates behaviour at the point of decision, enabling intervention before harmful outcomes materialise.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This prevention-first model is gaining attention as enterprises seek stronger protections against AI-assisted </span><a href="https://www.ibm.com/think/topics/cyber-attack" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">cyberattacks</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> and insider risks. The platform is already generally available across Windows, macOS, Linux, and browser-based deployments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:<a href="https://ventureburn.com/sharon-ai-raises-1-6-billion-ai-factory-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal"> Sharon AI Raises US$1.6B for AI Factory Expansion</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Investors Back Shift Toward Preventive Security</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors view Ent as part of a broader transformation within cybersecurity. Decibel Founding Partner Jon Sakoda said AI empowers attackers, driving demand for faster, advanced defensive security technologies globally.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Konstantin Buhler of Sequoia Partner noted the platforms capability to deliver AI reasoning directly to end devices and remarked that the paradigm shift from detection to prevention might be &#8220;the killer app for endpoints&#8221;.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Crosspoint Capital Partners stated that preventive security is becoming increasingly important as organizations look for a way to prevent an attack before it occurs instead of &#8220;forensic analysis after an event&#8221;.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In-Q-Tel commented on increasing demand from government customers for AI solutions. The investor sees real-time governance and forensic visibility as essential requirements for secure AI deployment.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ent’s advisory board includes former security leaders from Google, Aetna, MassMutual, Microsoft Azure Cloud Security, and the National Security Agency. Their expertise is expected to support the company’s next growth phase.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With fresh funding and early enterprise adoption already in place, Ent is positioning itself at the centre of a new cybersecurity category focused on understanding intent and preventing threats before they occur.</span></p>
